\title{RECP: Rank Energy Change Point Test for Multivariate Data}
\description{
This package provides nonparametric methods for detecting and locating a single change point in multivariate data sequences. The package implements a rank energy statistic constructed from multivariate ranks defined via optimal transport theory. The asymptotic null distribution is distribution-free, enabling universal rejection thresholds across different sample sizes. Two testing procedures are provided: a permutation-based test (REp) and a test based on simulating the limiting spectral distribution (REs). The methods are robust to heavy-tailed distributions and are accompanied by theoretical guarantees for change point location estimation.
